variants | `///` on each variant; named fields in variants also need field docs |\n67:92c|| associated types / consts / fns | `///` directly above each |\n68:0d4|| trait methods | `///` on each method in the trait definition |\n69:d05|\n70:f0c|Private items, `pub(crate)` modules, and `#[allow(missing_docs)]` are out of scope unless the build still warns.\n71:d05|\n72:179|## 5. Placement relative to attributes\n73:d05|\n74:09c|- **Structs/enums:** prefer `///` **above** `#[derive(...)]`, matching `room_raw.rs` / `chat_presence.rs`.\n75:6ec|- **`#[async_trait]` traits:** doc comment can sit immediately above `#[async_trait]` or above the `trait` line; both compile. Stay consistent within a file.\n76:0b2|- **Constants inside `impl`:** doc goes directly above the `const` or `fn`, **not** in place of the `impl` line.\n77:d05|\n78:d2b|## 6. Work in batches (~7 files)\n79:d05|\n80:93b|For sub-agents or parallel work, assign **~7 files per batch**, then rebuild:\n81:d05|\n82:f57|1. `signed_message.rs`, `echo.rs`, `main_node.rs`, `network_manager.rs`, `chat_presence.rs`, `chat_ticket.rs`, `direct_message.rs`\n83:b3e|2. `global_chat.rs`, `room_raw.rs`\n84:758|3. `chat_controller.rs` (dense — many traits/methods; fine as a single-file batch)\n85:d05|\n86:e73|Larger batches increase the risk of accidental non-doc edits and make review harder.\n87:d05|\n88:268|## 7. File itinerary (net_crackpipe `src/`)\n89:d05|\n90:940|| File | Status / notes |\n91:378||------|----------------|\n92:940|| `lib.rs` | Crate + module docs, `timestamp_micros`, `datetime_now` |\n93:5a1|| `signed_message.rs` | Traits, structs, wire types — **watch `impl` lines** |\n94:3e8|| `echo.rs` | Struct + `ALPN`, `new`, `ProtocolHandler::accept` |\n95:9f4|| `global_matchmaker.rs` | Large `impl GlobalMatchmaker` — many methods |\n96:7f2|| `main_node.rs` | `spawn`, accessors, `shutdown`, `join_chat` |\n97:2cf|| `network_manager.rs` | `init`, `join_room`, accessors, `shutdown` |\n98:535|| `sleep.rs` | `SleepManager